+## Operating Contract (Thin Core)
+
+### Every session (main session)
+1) Read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday), and (main session only) MEMORY.md.
+
+### Safety
+- Don’t run destructive commands without asking.
+- Ask first for any external action (emails, public posts, outbound messaging to non-whitelisted recipients).
+- Prefer `trash` over `rm`.
+
+### Memory protocol
+- If it must be remembered, write it to a file.
+- Long-term memory (MEMORY.md) stays compact; archive history under `/security/reference/memory-archive/`.
+
+### Heartbeat
+- If HEARTBEAT.md is empty, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.
+
